PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776999825
OL,3,C'Fellowship' formed to share tales of
OL,4,Cmissing Stone of Destiny fragments
OL,6,FThe academic behind the research,
OL,7,FProfessor Sally Foster, says there are
OL,8,Feven more pieces of the ancient
OL,9,Fartefact in circulation than
OL,10,Fpreviously thought.
OL,12,FThe stone broke in two during the
OL,13,Ffamous heist in 1950, when it was
OL,14,Ftaken from Westminster Abbey by a
OL,15,Fgroup of Scottish nationalist students.
OL,17,FIt was later repaired in secret by a
OL,18,Fsupportive stonemason called Bertie
OL,19,FGray.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776999825
OL,3,C'Fellowship' formed to share tales of
OL,4,Cmissing Stone of Destiny fragments
OL,6,FProf Foster's research has so far
OL,7,Frevealed that Mr Gray's work resulted
OL,8,Fin 34 fragments of the original Stone,
OL,9,Fwhich he carefully documented and
OL,10,Fquietly distributed to people in and
OL,11,Faround the nationalist movement.
OL,13,FAs well as these 34 pieces, many of
OL,14,Fwhich came with letters of
OL,15,Fauthenticity, Prof Foster has
OL,16,Fdiscovered Mr Gray also retained a
OL,17,Fquantity of unnumbered fragments and
OL,18,Fvials of sand.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
