PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776999825
OL,3,C'Fellowship' formed to share tales of
OL,4,Cmissing Stone of Destiny fragments
OL,6,FProf Foster's research has recently
OL,7,Fdiscovered the stone may have been
OL,8,Fbroken for a second time following the
OL,9,Fheist led by Ian Hamilton.
OL,11,FShe said: "As I learnt only a few
OL,12,Fweeks ago, there was yet another
OL,13,Funreported fracture episode.
OL,15,F"When the smaller part of the broken
OL,16,Fstone was carried into a Glasgow house
OL,17,Fto be hidden, Ian Hamilton and a
OL,18,Fcomrade dropped it and several pieces
OL,19,Fbroke off.
OL,26,@sD@KOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776999825
OL,3,C'Fellowship' formed to share tales of
OL,4,Cmissing Stone of Destiny fragments
OL,6,F"The family kept a fragment, and I can
OL,7,Fguess what probably happened to one of
OL,8,Fthe other pieces."
OL,10,FOne of the fragments ended up in the
OL,11,Ffamily of Ewen Traill, a student who
OL,12,Fhad been involved in briefly stealing
OL,13,Fthe sword of William Wallace and who
OL,14,Flater became a minister in Orkney.
OL,16,FThe story behind this, and the other
OL,17,Ffragments held by the fellowship, will
OL,18,Fbe explored in future research.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
