OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776999825
OL,3,C'Fellowship' formed to share tales of
OL,4,Cmissing Stone of Destiny fragments
OL,6,FOne of those who took part in the
OL,7,Ffellowship event said: "The stone has
OL,8,Fcome alive. I thought about it as a
OL,9,Fstory from the past ` but now I feel
OL,10,Fit is more dynamic."
OL,12,FAnother said: "The research and event
OL,13,Fhave allowed us to be more curious and
OL,14,Fless fearful of telling our tiny part
OL,15,Fof the story, and perhaps made us
OL,16,Fthink what we might do with our
OL,17,Ffragments in the future."
OL,26,@oD@XOUrD@TO]tD@OOUyD@YO]
